Italian Serie A champions, Juventus, is planning to sign Chelsea’s Jorginho in a swap deal for Miralem Pjanic, according to Sky Sports. Juventus coach, Maurizio Sarri, has indicated an interest in working with Jorginho again. Sarri and Jorginho both moved to Chelsea in the summer of 2018 from Napoli. Chelsea paid Napoli £50million plus £7million add-ons to sign Jorginho. Jorginho has three years left on his current contract with Chelsea. Juventus signed Pjanic from Roma for £25million in June 2016. Pjanic has one year left on his current contract with Juventus. The Bosnia-Herzegovina midfielder has also drawn the interest of Paris Saint-Germain.